   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-accepting" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_Salica.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-accepting-acceptted" mid="106" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="69"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>That's what I was about to tell you.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-a" mid="107" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="71"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>I left Merca when I was fifteen, saying that I'll come back after seeing the bigger world. My main goal was to broaden my perspective and gain knowledge and experience.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-b" mid="108" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="72"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>But all I saw in my journey was anxiety and fear wherever I went. No matter how peaceful the land was, no matter how strong the army was, countries could still be destroyed overnight if Goddess Vestinel or a Child became unhappy with them. You know the rules of this world.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-c" mid="109" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="73"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica${sound:npc_Salica_9807_qu_01.ogg}<BR>I heard so many mournings across Mistland and even saw with my own eyes the remains of countries that had been crushed under the goddess's orders. I realised that the reason why Merca and I were enjoying better fate was simply because of luck. Merca's peace can also be destroyed any time once the goddess changes her mind.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-d" mid="110" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="74"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica${sound:npc_Salica_9807_qu_02.ogg}<BR>After realising that, the goal of my trip changed to find a way to make Merca perfectly safe. I wandered for years without much progress until I heard a legend about a relic.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-e" mid="111" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="75"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>"Long ago, the southern lands had skilled master craftsmen along with a giant gemstone that shined with magnificent light. The craftsmen turned the gemstone into a statue and it repelled all the uninvited, even the children of the goddess. Peace lasted for ages in the southern lands."</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-f" mid="112" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="76"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>So you ended up in Chiron Island to search for the relic!</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-g" mid="113" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="77"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica${sound:npc_Salica_9807_qu_03.ogg}<BR>That's right. I was looking for the relic that repels the uninvited ones. <BR>For Merca's Heart to be safe, it needs to become independent, free from Childs' control.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-h" mid="114" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="78"><![CDATA[<html>$Vernicka${sound:npc_Vernicka_9807_qu_01.ogg}<BR>…Shalica, don't tell me you believe in that legend. You were gone for such a long time searching for a relic in tales of unknown origin?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-h" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-j" mid="116" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="80"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>There's enough proof. Similar legends are passed down in the northwestern regions and I even found written records with specific dates.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-i" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-1-k" mid="117" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="81"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>There was a time when Chiron Island used to be an independent state free from Childs' invasion. The dates match the records exactly and many witnesses tell of craftsmen who carried on their family business for generations in Chiron Island.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-1-j" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-2" mid="134" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="82"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>The reason why I didn't return to Merca until now was because people wouldn't have believed me without the evidence. But I've gathered enough information now and I'm sure we can find the relic if we search the island a little more.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-a" mid="119" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="83"><![CDATA[<html>$Vernicka$<BR>Sigh…. Let's suppose that the relic really exists in Chiron Island. What are you going to do after finding it?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-b" mid="120" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="84"><![CDATA[<html>$Vernicka$<BR>Chiron Island has long been occupied by Child Hirendel. That means even if the relic exists, it must have lost its power.<BR>Finding a useless relic won't solve anything. We would only be wasting our precious time.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-c" mid="121" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="85"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>I agree with Vernicka. It would be good if we can find it, of course… But we don’t know if things will go according to your plan.</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-d" mid="122" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="86"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>That's why I've been on good terms with the Anti-Goddess Faction. I'm sure their technology can restore the relic even if it's not working anymore.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-d" image="QN_Hologram.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-e" mid="123" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="87"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR><FONT color=#a82424>Lord Norfe</FONT>, the leader of Anti-Goddess Faction is more knowledgeable than you think. He is also the disciple of the court sorcerer of the old Arcadia. I'm sure he can restore the relic.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-f" mid="124" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="88"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>(Shalica knows Norfe's identity yet she's hiding it well.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-2-g" mid="125" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="89"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>If it really turns out to be a waste of time as Vernicka expects, than I will do whatever I can to find another way.<BR>I want to save Merca's Heart as much as you, Vernicka.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2367_vernicka-2-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2367_vernicka-3" mid="126" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="90"><![CDATA[<html>$Vernicka$<BR>Shalica…….</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-a" mid="147" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="136"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica${sound:npc_Salica_9807_qu_04.ogg}<BR>Vernicka, you're a leader who firmly keeps your place and withstands whatever comes your way. I can't be that kind of a leader. However, it's my role to take risks while you don't want to or can't.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-b" mid="148" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="137"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica${sound:npc_Salica_9807_qu_05.ogg}<BR>We should split our roles and do what we do best. I'll take the risk and find the relic, and restore it with the help of Anti-Goddess Faction. If things go wrong, you can make me take all the blame, and stand strong and continue to protect the people of Merca.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="Npc_Left_vernicka.dds" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-c" mid="149" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="138"><![CDATA[<html>$Vernicka$<BR>I can't do that, Shalica. How can I push you to such danger and malign you? That's…!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-d" mid="150" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="139"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>That's just the worst scenario. We should do our best to prevent that from happening. I'm sure we can do it. <FONT color=#387206>{user_nick}</FONT> and the Anti-Goddess Faction will be on our side too.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-e" mid="151" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="140"><![CDATA[<html>$Shalica$<BR>As the other leader of Merca, I want us to succeed. We will succeed. We will protect Merca and make it a safe and peaceful place.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-f" mid="152" select_type="4" />
      <talk_question mid="141"><![CDATA[<html>$Quest Completed$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n2351_salica-3-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="Npc_Right_Salica.dds" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n2351_salica-3-!next" mid="153" select_type="2" />
      <talk_question mid="142"><![CDATA[<html>${user_nick}$<BR><FONT color=#662500>Erm…. I was wondering...</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
